<TITLE> Five secretaries transferred </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 22 (bdnews24.com)Five secretaries have been shuffled, according to a circular released Wednesday by the establishment ministry. Communications secretary Mohammad Mahbubur Rahman and post & telecommunications secretary Iqbal Mahmood will transfer posts. ABM Abdul Haque Chowdhury, officer on special duty at the establishment ministry will replace secretary for religious affairs Md Ataur Rahman, who is set to retire on Nov 6. Primary and mass education secretary Muhammad Musharraf Hossain Bhuiyan has been transferred to the economic relations division while additional secretary of water resources Badrul Alam Tarofdar has been appointed as the secretary-in-charge at primary and mass education ministry. ERD secretary Aminul Islam Bhuiyan has been made OSD at the establishment ministry, after being appointed as alternative executive director of the Asian Development Bank. bdnews24.c
